
                                            Officials came to their rescue on Thursday afternoon in Porcupine Ravine.
                                         CAPE TOWN - Three men have been airlifted to safety after they got lost while hiking Table Mountain. Officials came to their rescue on Thursday afternoon in Porcupine Ravine. ER24 Spokesperson Russel Meiring said: “The AMS medical helicopter was called to airlift the patients and transport them to a nearby area to the awaiting ER24 paramedics. After all three men had been airlifted, paramedics assessed them and found that they had all escaped injury.”